variable.comment: Defined as a breast cancer from a Death or the first adjudication where the form 122 or 130 details indicate an invasive cancer. This file does not include cancers determined solely by the cause of death.

A description of the ICD site codes can be found in the reference file seer_icd_site_codes.dat by merging on the ICDCODE variable.

Evidence of Disease (SEER): digits 1-3 When size doesnt make sense, this field is used for other purposes (e.g. Leukemias have no size, this field records AIDS status). Size is usually measured in mm, though it may vary by cancer type. Even for cancers that do have a size, not all values indicate an actual size (e.g. 2 for many cancers means '<=2mm', but for breast cancer it means 'Mammographic diagnosis only, tumor not clinically palpable' ). WHI used the SEER 1988, 2nd edition rules for coding cancers. See the SEER coding section of the data prep/use document for details.
